subSubSection.paragraph:
Operculum (
Fig 1D
). Corneous, elongately ovate, nucleus apical.

Radula (
Fig 1E
). Rachidian teeth with three cusps. Two lateral cusps slightly stronger than the middle one, elevated from basal plate, forming a narrow concavity. The rightmost cusp with a small secondary cusp. Basal plate roughly rectangular, strongly concave along anterior edge. Lateral teeth with two strong cusps, outer one longer, but slightly thinner than inner one.

